<div id="review_68975271" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/68975271" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1534691-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1336530776p2/1534691.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/68975271?book_show_action=true">Aug 26, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/1534691-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer68975271" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13221700100435132264">A well written collection but I felt it sparse. The stories didn&apos;t seem like stories for the most part, except for &quot;Brother in the Basement&quot; which delved deep into the relationship between the narrator and his older brother. There were a bunch of scenes that tied together and brought up the consistent element of the narrator being too scared to disclose his sexuality and regretting the life he&apos;s lead in someways for his cowardice. <br/><br/>As a collection I felt it more like a novel that skips areas and </span>
  <span id="freeText13221700100435132264" style="display:none">A well written collection but I felt it sparse. The stories didn't seem like stories for the most part, except for "Brother in the Basement" which delved deep into the relationship between the narrator and his older brother. There were a bunch of scenes that tied together and brought up the consistent element of the narrator being too scared to disclose his sexuality and regretting the life he's lead in someways for his cowardice. <br /><br />As a collection I felt it more like a novel that skips areas and ties the one "theme" together. Not a bad read though.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13221700100435132264" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


